E2_E5_bridge.statement:
Assume H_seam (so |R|=N_can_prim). Then:
  (E5') residual can-cores inject into a set of size ≤ n·p ⇒ |R| ≤ n·p ⇒ residual mass (v14);
  (E2') residual can-cores inject into a set of size ≤ t·p ⇒ |R| ≤ t·p ⇒ residual mass + E1-scale D_prim budget;
  (E2)  residual supports inject into {0..t-1}×F_p ⇒ |R| ≤ t·p (rowsharp missing theorem form);
  (E5)  residual supports inject into D×F_p ⇒ |R| ≤ n·p.
Under H_seam, support injection and can-core injection are equivalent cardinality problems (bijection S ↔ C_can).
